1st ass

Design an IPv6 Network for 780 users using the available IPv6 address space

2001:db8:b:efe:1::/64

C: 780 users = 10 bits
S: 128 - 10 = /118
I: Ipasok si 4i sa 8th hex, 2nd hexadecimal
/118 = (8th, 2nd, 4i)

2001:0db8:000b:0efe:0001:0000:0000:0000/118

2001:0db8:000b:0efe:0001:0000:0400/118

NETWORK: 2001:0db8:000b:0efe:0001:0000:0000:0400/118
FIRST:   2001:0db8:000b:0efe:0001:0000:0000:0401/118
LAST:    2001:0db8:000b:0efe:0001:0000:0000:07FF/118
NOT:     2001:0db8:000b:0efe:0001:0000:0000:0800/118





2nd ass

Design an IPv6 Network for 78 sites using the IPv6 address space
2001:db8:2:5::/98

Determine the 3rd Site

C: 78 sites = 7 bits
A: /98 + 7 = /105
I: Ipasok si 8i sa 7th hex, 3rd hexadecimal


/105 = (7th, 3rd, 8i)

2001:0db8:0002:0005:0000:0000:0000:0000/105

2001:0db8:0002:0005:0000:0000:0080:0000/105

1st Site: 2001:0db8:0002:0005:0000:0000:0000:0000/105
2nd Site: 2001:0db8:0002:0005:0000:0000:0010:0000/105
3rd Site: 2001:0db8:0002:0005:0000:0000:0020:0000/105
4th Site: 2001:0db8:0002:0005:0000:0000:0030:0000/105

3RD SITE:

2001:0db8:0002:0005:0000:0000:0020:0000/105

NETWORK: 2001:0db8:0002:0005:0000:0000:0020:0000/105
FIRST:   2001:0db8:0002:0005:0000:0000:0020:0001/105
LAST:    2001:0db8:0002:0005:0000:0000:002F:FFFF/105
NOT:     2001:0db8:0002:0005:0000:0000:0030:0000/105
